What Makes This a "True" Interpreter?
Unlike our previous simple REPL script, this engine acts like real industrial code parsers:

Syntactic Decoupling: It doesn't use split() or string mutations. The Lexer scans individual code bytes and yields secure Token primitives.

Abstract Execution Maps: The text data converts into dynamic runtime configurations (VarAssignNode, PrintNode).

Hardware Isolation Layer: Memory allocation is governed and safely routed through private dictionary state stacks (self.environment and self.constants), protecting your computer from unsafe memory manipulation.
